csm_lib CHANGELOG
==================

- v1.0.0 | Mar 22 2026 (Phase 8):

  [New] csm_report_emit() — structured migration report: translated, gaps, captured, trust lists, hooks, neutralization, rollback, summary, CSM_RESULT line
  [New] csm_report_summary() — one-liner summary: "Translated: N | Gaps: N | Captured: N | Trust: N | Hooks: N | Neutralized: N"
  [New] CSM_RESULT machine-parseable line: CSM_RESULT:translated=N:gaps=N:captured=N:trust=N:hooks=N:neutralized=N
  [New] 10-report.bats — 10 tests: section presence, CSM_RESULT format, stdout fallback, empty-state header, summary format and count
  [Change] README.md — finalized API reference with all public functions, signatures, and report format

- v1.0.0 | Mar 22 2026 (Phase 7):

  [New] csm_neutralize() — full non-destructive disable (services, crons, executables) with FreeBSD guard and SELinux note
  [New] _csm_neutralize_crons() — chmod 000 cron files matching product prefix globs in /etc/cron.d/
  [New] _csm_neutralize_bins() — chmod 000 known executables per product (csf, lfd, cxs, cxswatch)
  [New] _csm_record_perms() — record original permissions in _CSM_NEUTRALIZE_LOG before chmod
  [New] Rollback command generation in report after neutralize
  [New] CSM_DRY_RUN=1 gate on neutralize functions (WOULD prefix, no file writes)
  [New] 08-neutralize.bats — 12 tests: perm recording, cron chmod, glob matching, dry-run gate, unknown product, SELinux note
  [New] 09-dryrun.bats — 9 tests: apply_var no-write, apply_all no-write, trust_allow no-write, neutralize no-chmod, log empty in dry-run, translation still runs, WOULD prefix in report

- v1.0.0 | Mar 22 2026 (Phase 6):

  [New] csm_report_add() — append line to report buffer
  [New] csm_apply_var() — set single variable in target config via pkg_config_set; dry-run safe
  [New] csm_apply_all() — apply all status=translated norm store entries to a config file
  [New] csm_apply_bfd_pressure() — write per-rule PRESSURE_TRIP overrides from _CSM_BFD_RULES/_CSM_BFD_TRIPS
  [New] csm_migrate_trust_allow() — csf.allow → allow_hosts.rules (pipe→colon, idempotent)
  [New] csm_migrate_trust_deny() — csf.deny → deny_hosts.rules (pipe→colon, temp entry TTL via date -d)
  [New] csm_migrate_trust_sips() — csf.sips → silent_ips.rules (direct copy with dedup)
  [New] csm_migrate_blocklists() — csf.blocklists 4-field → ipset.rules 7-field (hash:ip, DROP defaults)
  [New] csm_migrate_hooks() — csfpre/post → hook_pre/post (copy, chmod 750, /etc/csf/ path rewrite)
  [New] csm_migrate_lfd_ignore() — csf.ignore → allow.hosts (direct copy with dedup)
  [New] csm_migrate_cxs_ignore() — cxs.ignore keyword types → LMD ignore dat files
  [New] 06-trust-migrate.bats — 22 tests: pipe→colon, CRLF, idempotency, blocklist expand, CXS ignore types, ip: skip
  [New] 07-hooks.bats — 7 tests: copy, chmod 750, path rewrite, missing hook graceful handling

- v1.0.0 | Mar 22 2026 (Phase 5):

  [New] _csm_map_lmd_init() — CXS→LMD mapping table (~27 entries: quarantine, alerts, scanner, scheduling, suspend, inotify/watch, gap vars)
  [New] csm_translate_lmd() — multi-file scan (cxs.defaults + cxswatch.conf merge), CXS_WATCH→monitor_mode transform, bytes→k conversion, scan_yara auto-set, cxswatch.sh CLI capture
  [New] 05-translate-lmd.bats — 13 tests: direct maps, CXS_WATCH=1→users, CXS_WATCH=0→disabled, bytes→k, scan_yara, gap vars, script CLI, total count, missing-file, re-entry safety

- v1.0.0 | Mar 22 2026 (Phase 4):

  [New] _csm_map_bfd_init() — LFD→BFD mapping table (8 pressure entries, 5 direct entries, 1 fixed entry)
  [New] csm_translate_bfd() — pressure model formula (trip = min(trigger * 3, 200)), direct and fixed mappings
  [New] 04-translate-bfd.bats — 8 tests: pressure calibration, clamp boundary, trigger=0, direct BAN_TTL/EMAIL_ADDRESS, LF_SELECT→FIREWALL=apf

- v1.0.0 | Mar 22 2026 (Phase 3):

  [New] _csm_xfm_apply() — transform dispatcher (direct, direct+egf, direct+rgt, append_s, sep_semi_colon, expand_drop, parse_rate, gap, log_bfd)
  [New] _csm_map_apf_init() — CSF→APF mapping table (~40 entries across port filtering, network, protection, SMTP, deny/expiry, gap vars, LFD redirects)
  [New] csm_translate_apf() — bulk translation with full normalization pass; unmapped vars receive status "unmapped"
  [New] 03-translate-apf.bats — 16 tests covering all transform types, gap, log_bfd, unmapped, re-entry safety
  [Change] tests/fixtures/csf/csf.conf — added SMTP_ALLOWGROUP, UDPFLOOD_BURST, UDPFLOOD_ALLOWUSER for full mapping table coverage

- v1.0.0 | Mar 22 2026 (Phase 2):

  [New] csm_detect_csf(), csm_detect_lfd(), csm_detect_cxs() — product detection
  [New] csm_read_var() — single-var Perl-style + shell-style config parser with CRLF handling
  [New] csm_read_conf() — bulk config parser with CRLF handling
  [New] _csm_read_cxs_ignore() — CXS keyword-based ignore file parser
  [New] _csm_norm_add(), _csm_norm_find() — normalization store helpers
  [New] Test fixtures: mock CSF config, trust lists, hooks, CXS config, ignore files
  [New] 01-detection.bats (11 tests), 02-config-parse.bats (18 tests)

- v1.0.0 | Mar 22 2026 (Phase 1):

  [New] Initial release — ConfigServer Migration Library
  [New] CSF/LFD/CXS detection via config file and binary checks
  [New] Perl-style and shell-style config parser (csm_read_var, csm_read_conf)
  [New] CSF→APF variable translation (~40 mapped, data-driven tables)
  [New] LFD→BFD pressure model translation (threshold→trip formula)
  [New] CXS→LMD variable translation (~30 mapped, multi-file scan)
  [New] Trust list migration (allow, deny, silent IPs, blocklists)
  [New] Hook script migration (copy, chmod 750, path rewrite)
  [New] CXS ignore file translation to LMD format
  [New] Non-destructive neutralization (services, crons, executables)
  [New] Full dry-run mode via CSM_DRY_RUN=1
  [New] Structured migration report with CSM_RESULT machine-parseable line
  [New] Full variable normalization — all vars captured even without mapping
